==West Makian==
===Etymology===
Together with the polite {{m|mqs|baba|t=father}}, likely borrowed from {{der|mqs|tft|yaya|t=mother}}.
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|mqs|/ˈja.ja/}}
===Noun===
{{head|mqs|noun}}
# [[mother]]
====Usage notes====
The term ''yaya'' is used for addressing one's mother, whereas the terms {{m|mqs|mama}} and {{m|mqs|mamu}} are used for referring to a mother.
